snippet.title: Asterisk no Daibouken (Game Processor SNES User Game) OST
snippet.description:
Asterisk no Daibouken
アスタリスクの大冒險 / Asterisk's Great Adventure

The Nintendo Game Processor is a standalone SNES development kit system that includes the software Mario Factory that allows easy creation of games with an interface similar to Mario Paint, and put them on a RAM cartridge where they could be played on retail SNES consoles. Think of it like a sort of even easier to use Net Yaroze.
It also has a music maker similar to Mario Paint and Wario Ware DIY but produces music with a very regular SNES Nintendo soundfont.

This game is the only dump we could get from a Game Processor RAM Cassette, used for storing games on the Game Processor system.

More information (as well as download of the ROM and music) can be found in my research here:
https://luigiblood.neocities.org/gameprocessor
